stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> INPUTS

    INPUTS --> WALKING_CHECK: In:\n- motion_level\n- micro_state\n- zone\nOut:\n- branch selection

    WALKING_CHECK --> WALKING: micro_state == MACRO_PHASE\nAND motion_level > restless_max\nAND ("Transit" in zone OR "Floor" in zone)\nOutput: label=WALKING, score=0.90, is_walking=true
    WALKING_CHECK --> NORMALIZE: otherwise

    NORMALIZE --> RESTING_CHECK: motion_score = clamp(motion_level / restless_max, 0, 1)

    RESTING_CHECK --> RESTING: motion_score < (rest_max / restless_max)\nOutput: label=RESTING, is_walking=false
    RESTING_CHECK --> SHIFTING: motion_score >= (rest_max / restless_max)\nOutput: label=SHIFTING, is_walking=false

    WALKING --> [*]
    RESTING --> [*]
    SHIFTING --> [*]

    note right of NORMALIZE
      Formula:
      motion_score = min(1.0, motion_level / max(restless_max, 1e-9))
    end note

    note right of RESTING_CHECK
      Label threshold:
      resting_cutoff = rest_max / max(restless_max, 1e-9)
      if motion_score < resting_cutoff -> RESTING
      else -> SHIFTING
    end note

    note right of WALKING
      Walking is a gated override path.
      It bypasses normalization output and emits
      a fixed score of 0.90 in current implementation.
    end note
